2.name: DDMMYY
2.desc: Calendar date: D = Day; M = Month; Y = Year.

3.name: MMDDYY
3.desc: Calendar date: M = Month; D = Day; Y = Year.

4.name: DDMMCCYY
4.desc: Calendar date C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month; D=Day.

5.name: DDMMCCYYHHMM
5.desc:
Calendar date and time: C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month; D=Day; H=Hour;
                                    M=Minute.

6.name: CCYYMMB
6.desc:
Half-month: CC=century YY=year MM=month, B=1:first half month,
                                    B=2:second half month.

7.name: CCYYMMW
7.desc:
Week within a calendar month: CC=century YY=year MM=month. W=1-5 first
                                    week to fifth week in a month.

8.name: CCYYMMDDS
8.desc:
Shift within a calendar day: CC=century YY=year MM=month DD=day S=1-9
                                    shift in a day.

9.name: CCYYMMDDPP
9.desc:
Time period within a calendar day: CC=century YY=year MM=month DD=day
                                    PP=00-99 time period.

10.name: CCYYMMDDTHHMM
10.desc:
Calendar date including time with minutes: C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month;
                                    D=Day; T=Time designator; H=Hour; M=Minutes. The character [T] shall be used as time
                                    designator to indicate the start of the representation of the time. For example:
                                    20010912T1433.

101.name: YYMMDD
101.desc: Calendar date: Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day.

102.name: CCYYMMDD
102.desc: Calendar date: C = Century ; Y = Year ; M = Month ; D = Day.

103.name: YYWWD
103.desc:
Calendar week day: Y = Year ; W = Week ; D = Day Week number 01 is
                                    always first week of January Day number 1 is always Monday.

105.name: YYDDD
105.desc:
Calendar day: Y = Year ; D = Day January the first = Day 001 Always
                                    start numbering the days of the year from January 1st through December 31st.

106.name: MMDD
106.desc: Day of a month: M = Month; D = Day.

107.name: DDD
107.desc: Day's number within a specific year: D = Day.

108.name: WW
108.desc: Week's number within a specific year: W = Week.

109.name: MM
109.desc: Month's number within a specific year: M = Month.

110.name: DD
110.desc: Day's number within is a specific month: D = Day.

201.name: YYMMDDHHMM
201.desc:
Calendar date including time without seconds: Y = Year; M = Month; D =
                                    Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

202.name: YYMMDDHHMMSS
202.desc:
Calendar date including time with seconds: Y = Year; M = Month; D =
                                    Day; H = Hour; m = Minutes = Seconds.

203.name: CCYYMMDDHHMM
203.desc:
Calendar date including time with minutes: C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month;
                                    D=Day; H=Hour; M=Minutes.

204.name: CCYYMMDDHHMMSS
204.desc:
Calendar date including time with seconds: C=Century;Y=Year;
                                    M=Month;D=Day;H=Hour;M=Minute;S=Second.

205.name: CCYYMMDDHHMMZHHMM
205.desc:
Calendar date including time and time zone expressed in hours and
                                    minutes. ZHHMM = time zone given as offset from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

305.name: MMDDHHMM
305.desc: Month, day, hours, minutes; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

306.name: DDHHMM
306.desc: Day, hours, minutes; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

401.name: HHMM
401.desc: Time without seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute.

402.name: HHMMSS
402.desc: Time with seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute; s = Seconds.

406.name: ZHHMM
406.desc:
Offset from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) where Z is plus (+) or
                                    minus (-).

501.name: HHMMHHMM
501.desc: Time span without seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute;.

502.name: HHMMSS-HHMMSS
502.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the
                                    end time (both expressed by hours minutes and seconds). Data is to be transmitted as
                                    consecutive characters without hyphen.

503.name: HHMMSSZZZ-HHMMSSZZZ
503.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the
                                    end time (both expressed by hours minutes, seconds and time zone). Data is to be
                                    transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

602.name: CCYY
602.desc: Calendar year including century: C = Century; Y = Year.

603.name: YYS
603.desc: Semester in a calendar year: Y = Year; S = Semester.

604.name: CCYYS
604.desc: Semester in a calendar year: C = Century; Y = Year; S = Semester.

608.name: CCYYQ
608.desc: Quarter in a calendar year: C = Century; Y = Year; Q = Quarter.

609.name: YYMM
609.desc: Month within a calendar year: Y = Year; M = Month.

610.name: CCYYMM
610.desc: Month within a calendar year: CC = Century; Y = Year; M = Month.

613.name: YYMMA
613.desc:
To specifiy a ten-day period within a month of a year (A = ten day
                                    period).

614.name: CCYYMMA
614.desc:
To specifiy a ten-day period within a month of a year, including
                                    century (A = ten day period).

615.name: YYWW
615.desc:
Week within a calendar year: Y = Year; W = Week 1st week of January =
                                    week 01.

616.name: CCYYWW
616.desc:
Week within a calendar year: CC = Century; Y = Year; W = Week (1st
                                    week of January = week 01).

701.name: YY-YY
701.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start year followed by the
                                    end year (both without century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters
                                    without hyphen.

702.name: CCYY-CCYY
702.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start year followed by the
                                    end year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive
                                    characters without hyphen.

703.name: YYS-YYS
703.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start semester of a year
                                    followed by the end semester of a year (both not including century). Data is to be
                                    transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

704.name: CCYYS-CCYYS
704.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start semester of a year
                                    followed by the end semester of a year (both including century). Data is to be
                                    transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

705.name: YYPYYP
705.desc: Format of period to be given without hyphen (P = period of 4 months).

706.name: CCYYP-CCYYP
706.desc: Format of period to be given without hyphen (P = period of 4 months).

707.name: YYQ-YYQ
707.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start quarter of a year
                                    followed by the end quarter of year (both not including century). Data is to be
                                    transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

708.name: CCYYQ-CCYYQ
708.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start quarter of a year
                                    followed by the end quarter of year (both including century). Data is to be
                                    transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

709.name: YYMM-YYMM
709.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start month of a year
                                    followed by the end month of a year (both not including century). Data is to be
                                    transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

710.name: CCYYMM-CCYYMM
710.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start month of a year
                                    followed by the end month of a year (both including century). Data is to be
                                    transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

711.name: CCYYMMDD-CCYYMMDD
711.desc: Format of period to be given in actual message without hyphen.

713.name: YYMMDDHHMM-YYMMDDHHMM
713.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the
                                    end time (format year, month, day, hour and minute). Data is to be transmitted as
                                    consecutive characters without hyphen.

715.name: YYWW-YYWW
715.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start week of a year followed
                                    by the end week of year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as
                                    consecutive characters without hyphen.

716.name: CCYYWW-CCYYWW
716.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start week of a year followed
                                    by the end week of year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as
                                    consecutive characters without hyphen.

717.name: YYMMDD-YYMMDD
717.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start date followed by the
                                    end date (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive
                                    characters without hyphen.

718.name: CCYYMMDD-CCYYMMDD
718.desc:
A period of time specified by giving the start date followed by the
                                    end date (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive
                                    characters without hyphen.

719.name: CCYYMMDDHHMM-CCYYMMDDHHMM
719.desc:
A period of time which includes the century, year, month, day, hour
                                    and minute. Format of period to be given in actual message without hyphen.

720.name: DHHMM-DHHMM
720.desc:
Format of period to be given without hyphen (D=day of the week,
                                    1=Monday; 2=Tuesday; ... 7=Sunday).

801.name: Year
801.desc: To indicate a quantity of years.

802.name: Month
802.desc: To indicate a quantity of months.

803.name: Week
803.desc: To indicate a quantity of weeks.

804.name: Day
804.desc: To indicate a quantity of days.

805.name: Hour
805.desc: To indicate a quantity of hours.

806.name: Minute
806.desc: To indicate a quantity of minutes.

807.name: Second
807.desc: To indicate a quantity of seconds.

808.name: Semester
808.desc: To indicate a quantity of semesters (six months).

809.name: Four months period
809.desc: To indicate a quantity of four months periods.

810.name: Trimester
810.desc: To indicate a quantity of trimesters (three months).

811.name: Half month
811.desc: To indicate a quantity of half months.

812.name: Ten days
812.desc: To indicate a quantity of ten days periods.
